LAFIA – Abdullahi Sule, the governor of Nasarawa State has said on Monday that his administration would be partnering with Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) and the international donors to funds the development of agricultural value chain programme in the state.
The governor who made the assertion during the official flag-off of fertilizer seeds for the 2019 cropping season in Lafia, added that the programme was expected to increase the production of farm produce in the state.
“I have already given the approval for the state government to partner the Federal Government of Nigeria and international organisation for the fund of agricultural development to implement the value chain development program (VCDP).
“This is expected to increase the income of every household that engages in the production and marketing of rice and cassava in Nasarawa State,” he said.
Governor Sule, explained that the state government has signed a Memorandum of Understand with the Federal Government, adding that the state government has released N88 million as its counterpart payment for the take-off of the programme.
Mean while, the state government has launched the sale of fertilizer directly to farmers at the rate of N3,500, urging the committee to strictly comply with government’s directive as its administration would not tolerate any form of diversion of the product.